  "title": "Safety Officer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description &amp; Requirements</strong></p>\n<p>· To develop &amp; implement Health, Safety and Environment (HSE) policy, programs &amp;</p>\n<p>procedures</p>\n<p>· To ensure all safety matters are in compliance with statutory, contractual &amp;</p>\n<p>management system requirements</p>\n<p>· To oversee and lead the Safety team in the implementation of company’s safety</p>\n<p>system at project sites</p>\n<p>· To conduct toolbox meetings</p>\n<p>· Perform construction site safety inspections &amp; attend site walks with client &amp;</p>\n<p>subcons</p>\n<p>· Identify unsafe work practice and work condition &amp; recommend control measures</p>\n<p>to project team</p>\n<p>· Prepare/Review Risk Assessment/SWP/Method Statement/Permit-to-Work for all</p>\n<p>project works. Manage and maintain/update these safety records &amp; checklists</p>\n<p>· Inventory management for Personal Protective Equipment (PPE)</p>\n<p>· Support haze and pandemic activities</p>\n<p>· Respond promptly to incidents &amp; accidents</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<p>· WSQ Advanced Certificate in WSH or its equivalent</p>\n<p>· Registered WSHC/WSHO with MOM, ECO with NEA</p>\n<p>· Have a good knowledge in Occupational Health &amp; Safety Management System</p>\n<p>· Have excellent people management &amp; interpersonal skills</p>",
